## Proposed Changes

We will generate the Android codebase using the requested folder structure:
`app/src/main/java/com/interview/platform/ui/screens/[module_name]/[screen_name]/`

Each screen will be fully provisioned with:
- `[ScreenName]UiState.kt` (Modeling loading, empty, error, and success states)
- `[ScreenName]ViewModel.kt` (StateFlow management and Hilt injection)
- `[ScreenName]Screen.kt` (Compose UI adhering to Material 3 tokens)

### Phase 1: Authentication & Profile
**Modules**: MOD-01, MOD-02
- `SplashScreen`, `WelcomeScreen`, `LoginScreen`, `OtpVerificationScreen`, `PermissionsScreen`, `ProfileScreen`, `EditProfileScreen`.

### Phase 2: Interview Configuration
**Modules**: MOD-03, MOD-04, MOD-05, MOD-09
- `HomeDashboardScreen`, `DepartmentSelectionScreen`, `TechnologySelectionScreen`, `ExperienceSelectionScreen`, `QuestionCountSelectionScreen`, `InterviewSummaryScreen`.

### Phase 3: Mock Interview
**Modules**: MOD-10, MOD-11, MOD-12, MOD-13
- `InterviewSessionScreen`, `VoiceRecordingScreen`, `AudioReviewScreen`, `SpeechToTextScreen`, `QuestionSubmittedScreen`, `InterviewCompletedScreen`.

### Phase 4: Evaluation & Feedback
**Modules**: MOD-14, MOD-15, MOD-16
- `ResultsDashboardScreen`, `DetailedEvaluationScreen`, `QuestionWiseAnalysisScreen`, `StrengthAnalysisScreen`, `WeaknessAnalysisScreen`, `AiFeedbackReportScreen`.

### Phase 5: Recommendations
**Modules**: MOD-19
- `LearningRecommendationsScreen`, `InterviewRoadmapScreen`, `RecommendedTechnologiesScreen`, `PracticePlanScreen`.

### Phase 6: History & Analytics
**Modules**: MOD-17, MOD-18, MOD-20
- `InterviewHistoryScreen`, `PerformanceAnalyticsScreen`, `AchievementsScreen`.

## UI/UX Design Theme Implementation
- **Colors**: Primary (`#16A34A`), Secondary (`#475569`), Background (`#F8FAFC`), Surface (`#FFFFFF`), Success (`#22C55E`), Warning (`#F59E0B`), Error (`#DC2626`).
- **Typography**: Inter (Google Fonts via Compose Downloadable Fonts).
- **Accessibility**: Enforced 48dp minimum touch targets, proper `contentDescription` on all interactive elements, and Compose `semantics`.

